@Œ† It is the definition of conservative, it makes no statement except for the continuation of the status quo.

Saying that "all extremism is bad" is a conservative moral judgment, since it posits that any political statement or action beyond a certain level of familiarity (i.e. something 'too extreme') is bad.

It does not take into account historical extremes that had to be undertaken to prevent human suffering.  Ending chattel slavery in the US was once an "extremist position" as was "dismantling and ending the third reich".  There are countless examples where extreme political action resulted in historical good for humanity, and indeed often required violence to come about.
